Residents of Hillbrow have taken to the streets yet again. This time, they are protesting against rampant drug dealing and usage in the area.  They marched to the Hillbrow police station calling for it to be shut down. Residents accuse the police of being corrupt and being in cahoots with drug dealers. Earlier this week angry residents torched two businesses owned by Nigerian nationals accusing them of being drug dens. They say they want drugs out of their community. Watch video below: 